  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dba \u0dad\u0dc0\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0da7\u0dad\u0dca \u0d8b\u0dab\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The battle for British Prime Minister continues to heat up",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former British finance minister Rishi Sunak is leading the race to replace Boris Johnson as leader of the Conservative Party and prime minister after winning the most votes in the second round of voting.",
        "Sunak came first with 101 votes, followed by junior trade minister Penny Mordont with 83 votes and foreign secretary Liz Truss with 64 votes. Attorney General Zuela Braverman left with 27 votes.",
        "Also, Legislator Tom Tugenhut received 32 votes and Kemi Bednow received 49 votes."
      ],
